      {
        "id": 2812190,
        "name": "J@son Tr@ughber",
        "username": "Jason_T",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/jason_t/{size}/2319_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-02-07T23:41:08.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I\u2019m just now starting to play around with Burgundy.  Have really enjoyed the few Chambolle Musigny that I\u2019ve tried.</p>\n<p>Am keen on trying Bertheau\u2019s wines, and had a chance to get some \u201818s when they came out a couple weeks ago, but didn\u2019t pull the trigger as I\u2019m still skittish on the vintage based on the limited bit I\u2019ve heard so far.</p>",
