      {
        "id": 2812245,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-02-08T01:00:35.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"9\" data-topic=\"158255\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Am keen on trying Bertheau\u2019s wines, and had a chance to get some \u201818s when they came out a couple weeks ago, but didn\u2019t pull the trigger as I\u2019m still skittish on the vintage based on the limited bit I\u2019ve heard so far.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Bertheau did very well in 2017, 2016 and 2015, so it might be worth considering backfilling rather than chasing the 2018s\u2026</p>\n<p>Fran\u00e7ois\u2019 father\u2019s wines were frequently superb, by the way, so don\u2019t hesitate if you ever see any.</p>",
